====Noun====
{{ja-noun|おと}}

# a younger sibling

====See also====
* {{ja-r|劣る|おとる}}

===Etymology 2===
otopito > otoɸito > otowito > *otowuto > otouto > otoːto. Compound of {{term|弟||younger sibling|tr=oto|lang=ja}} and {{term|人||person|tr=pito|lang=ja}}.

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|おとうと}}

# one’s own younger brother
# a younger male

=====Usage notes=====
Used when referring to one’s own younger brother; to refer to another’s younger brother, one uses {{term|弟さん|lang=ja|tr=otōtosan}}, while when ''addressing'' one’s own younger brother, one uses their given name, such as {{term|太郎|lang=ja|tr=Tarō}}. Contrast with addressing one’s own older brother, when one uses the honorific {{term|お兄さん|lang=ja|tr=oniisan}}.

